Metatibia much larger than mesotibia (
Fig. 20
). Elytron at humerus with minute denticle. Male: TA of aedeagus (
Figs 88, 90
) with moderately long flagellum; scleritecomplex at base of flagellum in repose subparallel with apodeme of aedeagus. Apical scoop of pedon subtrapezoid or subtriangular, without distinct median extension. (
Fig. 162
). Tergite VIII apically weakly concave. Female: Setose patch of venter consisting of 3 single rows of modified setae. Tergite VIII apically subtruncate, very weakly concave. Length of ductus spermathecae plus spermatheca 2.7–3.7 X as long as tergite VIII.
